name: Margaret River Visitors Centre
directions: Inside the Visitors Centre.
comment: Gender neutral accessible and ambulant single stalls.   Accessible stall has grabrails, lowered basin and hand dryer.   Both have rubbish bins and sanitary disposal.  Available 9-5, 7 days.   Free street parking.   Designated disabled parking available behind the Center in  Tunbridge St, with walkway to Centre.   The main street has quite a steep slope.   No parenting facilities.

name: Science Building, room 110
directions: first floor next to glass-panelled office space
comment:
At the moment, the building is still under renovation and the English department is currently stationed there. You may have to ask for someone in the English Department's office to open the door since the lock system is accessed with a card (which is extremely problematic); It should be able to open from the outside and lock from the inside soon (written as of 10/9). 

Because UH's nondiscrimination statement includes gender identity and expression, students, staff and faculty are free to use the restroom of their choice. For those preferring more privacy, we are providing the following information. Lean more at: http://www.uh.edu/lgbtq/transgender_affairs/
